Like most other people, i played this on Xbox 360 and did more than 300+ hours of playtime, the reason being is because this is what i looked forward to when i got home, a lot of role playing games do have their downside, this included, yet it still holds it's own, against even Skryim i imagine!

Combat;

The combat is really rewarding, you have your three types, magic caster, melee with sharp or blunt weapons and a ranged fighter with arrows and daggers, yet it works those really really well, the system for magic is using stamina as a resource, which is a good idea in my opinion, but it is bothersome mainly because in tough fights you want a lot of stamina and with the constant running around it drains rapidly, forcing you to pick a good spot and be careful with what you do before you take a giant limb to the face, the animations for magic are incredible and at later levels you feel overpowered, yet you are still very fragile, and monsters can still rip you apart (Bitterblack isle is probably the biggest example, looking at you Death, Daimon and the ur dragon) so you will need to think clever, and it is a very different story for all vocations, although the higher ones have more abilities and deal more damage, a melee in this feels completely different to a ranged, unlike other games where you spam the same buttons. Climbing is a thing that you can do on almost all monsters (others you pick up) and can deal damage, but there is something that leaves me positively throbbing about walking around with my pawns, quite happily taking in the scenery, when a big ♥♥♥♥ing griffin comes out of nowhere and is on you before you can shout GREAT GOOGLEY MOOGLY" although some bosses are overpowered

